"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-07-31-simone-biles-mykayla-skinner-olympics-gold\", \"text\": \"The uncontested G.O.A.T. of American women's gymnastics,Simone Biles,has seemingly responded to an unsavory remark made by a former Team USA teammate of hers.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBesides Simone, I feel like the talent and the depth just isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t like what it used to be,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d her former teammate, MyKayla Skinner said in a YouTube video posted after the team selection.\\u00c2\\u00a0Skinner, who earned a silver medal on the vault at the Tokyo Olympics, said in the since-deleted video.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cA lot of girls don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t work as hard. The girls just don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have the work ethic.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Biles seemed to clap back at the time witha postshared to social platform Threads, writing, \\\"Not everyone needs a mic and a platform.\\\"\\u00c2  Following the women's all-around gold medalvictory\\u00c2\\u00a0at the Paris Olympics on Tuesday, Biles took to her Instagram account to shareimagesof the squad \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 including herself, Jordan Chiles, Suni Lee, Jade Carey and Hezly Rivera \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 celebrating their win, which earned Biles' her eighth gold medal and the title of most-decorated American Olympics gymnast of all time.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\\"Lack of talent, lazy, olympic champions,\\\" Biles captioned her post, an ostensible reference to comments made by Skinner.  https://www.instagram.com/p/C-ESNIFIQ8l/  While Skinner initially defended her remarks, she later apologized in a statement shared to X/Twitter after receiving an adverse public response.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt was not my intention to offend of disrespect any of the athletes or to take away from their hard work,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she wrote. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI take full responsibility for what I said and I deeply apologize.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The latest development in the simmering tension between the two athletes came on Wednesday, when Biles claimed that Skinner had blocked her Instagram account. \\\"Oop I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve been blocked,\\\" Bilestweeted,along with several emojis. Chiles separately posted an image on her Instagram story of someone holding what appears to be Biles phone clicked into Skinner's account, which is inaccessible. \\\"When she blocks Simone,\\\" Chiles captioned the post.\\u00c2  oop I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve been blocked \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u0080\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00ab\\u00a2\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0082  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Simone Biles (@Simone_Biles)July 31, 2024    \\u00c2  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC. Reproduction of material from any Salon pages without written permission is strictly prohibited. SALON \\u00c2\\u00ae is registered in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office as a trademark of Salon.com, LLC. Associated Press articles: Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2016 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.  DMCA Policy  By subscribing, you agree that Salon will automatically charge you at the then-current rate (currently $9.95/month or $95/year) each month/year until you cancel. Log in to your account anytime to cancel prior to renewal date and avoid future charges.  Your current signup type is\"}"